############################### File Handling #######################################

# Files are used to store the data permanently
# There are two types of file: Text file and Binary file
# Text file is used to store character data
# Binary file is used to store image, video 

# open(): f=open(file_name,mode) 

# There are different types of modes for text files:

# r: opens file in read mode
#  : pointer is always at begining position
#  : if the specified file doesnt not exist then, we will get FileNotFoundError.

# w: opens file in write mode
#  : if file contains some data then it overrides it.
#  : if file not present then creates the new file.

# a: opens the file in append mode
#  : if file already conatins data, then it doesnt override it.
#  : if specified file doesnt exist then creates new file

# r+: to read and write the data
#   : pointer will be placed at the begining 
#   : write will override the old data 
#   : if file is not found then we will get FileNotFoundError

# w+: to write and read the file
#   : first old data will be overriden before writing and then read
#   : if the specified file not found then it will create new file.

# a+: it will append and read the file 
#   : it will write without overriding existing data and then read.
#   : if file already exist then we will get FileError.

# x: opens file exclusive creation mode 
#  : if the file already exist then gives the FileExistError.

# For binary files, just append the b to the existing modes.

# close(). f.close() is used to close the file to free the system resources

# Various Properties of File Object:
# f.name --> returns file name
# f.mode --> returns the mode in which file is opened
# f.closed --> return boolean value to indicate whether file is closed or not
# f.readable --> returns boolean value to indicate file is readable or not
# f.writable --> returns boolean value to indicate file is writable or not

